Description: The default-github threat model shares multiple threats with other industry-standard threat models, particularly in web application security.
There are overlapping mitigation strategies identified in both the default-github model and other industry threat models.
The threat model aligns with compliance frameworks such as GDPR and HIPAA, indicating shared risks and mitigation strategies.

Source: A growing trend of API abuse and insufficient rate limiting across various applications.
Frequent occurrences of XSS and SQL Injection across multiple threat models.
